In Western Australia
we have a lot of
different reptiles that
exist in the state

PTO







Bobtail Lizard:

The bobtail lizard is a
lizard with a big fat
tail that looks similar
to its head, is the tail
is bitten the lizard will
detatch the tail and
will grow back in time...
Another fact, their
bite strength is
fucking painful.

Blue Tongue Lizard:

A lizard with a blue
tongue, the colour of
the tongue to other
animals shows up as a
bright pink which is a
sign of poison or
danger so other
animals were to be
warry and stay away.
